  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Child Health in Rural Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will improve the lives of the needy children in rural Uganda by promoting water, sanitation and hygiene  (WASH) activities in households, encourage immunization, providing mosquito nets, educating proper feeding in children, promoting and providing de-worming tablets. The project will also sensitize community members on proper toilet use, boiling drinking water, hand washing with soap after critical moments, protecting and maintaining of water quality from source to point of use.</narrative>
  </description>
